Now we can complete the proof of `le_antisymm`.
We need to show `I = J`.
We have `h_final_left : ŌłĆ N Ōłł J, N Ōłł I` and `h_final_right : ŌłĆ N Ōłł I, N Ōłł J`.
This means `I` and `J` are subsets of each other, so they are equal.

