```tactics
def IsRefinement (DŌéü DŌéé : DirectSumDecomposition M) : Prop :=
  ŌłĆ Ō”āNŌ”ä, N Ōłł DŌéé ŌåÆ Ōłā B : Set (PersistenceSubmodule M), B ŌŖå DŌéü Ōł¦ N = sSup B
```

So, `IsRefinement J I` means that for any `N Ōłł I`, there exists a subset `B` of `J` such that `N = sSup B`. This is the wrong direction. This means that `I` is a refinement of `J`.

Wait, no. The definition is `ŌłĆ N Ōłł DŌéé, Ōłā B ŌŖå DŌéü, N = sSup B`. So, `IsRefinement DŌéü DŌéé` means that `DŌéü` is a refinement of `DŌéé`.

So, `h_J_le_I : I Ōēż J` means that `I` is a refinement of `J`. So, for any `N Ōłł I`, we must have `N Ōłł J`.

This is exactly the goal. So, to prove `ŌłĆ N Ōłł I, N Ōłł J`, we can use the fact that `I Ōēż J`.

